<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="elevation range">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Elevation range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Ca. 20 m in Korea. 30 m to 650 m in Russia, Japan, and Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" author="Przhiboro, AA" editor="Lantsov, V" journalOrPublisher="Zoosymposia" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="221 - 228" refId="B47" refString="Przhiboro, AA, Paramonov, NM, Bazova, N, 2009. Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae). In: Lantsov, V, Ed., Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889-1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909-1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909-1994). Zoosymposia 3: 221 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" title="Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" volume="3" volumeTitle="Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889 - 1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909 - 1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909 - 1994)." year="2009">Przhiboro et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="period of activity">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Period of activity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Beginning of August in Korea. June-July in Russia, Japan, and Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" author="Przhiboro, AA" editor="Lantsov, V" journalOrPublisher="Zoosymposia" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="221 - 228" refId="B47" refString="Przhiboro, AA, Paramonov, NM, Bazova, N, 2009. Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae). In: Lantsov, V, Ed., Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889-1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909-1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909-1994). Zoosymposia 3: 221 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" title="Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" volume="3" volumeTitle="Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889 - 1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909 - 1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909 - 1994)." year="2009">Przhiboro et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Unknown in Korea. Shores of different types of running waters, from shores of large- and medium-sized rivers on plains to medium-sized and small rivers in the foothills in boreal forest, mixed forest, forest-steppe, and steppe landscape zones in Russia and Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" author="Przhiboro, AA" editor="Lantsov, V" journalOrPublisher="Zoosymposia" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="221 - 228" refId="B47" refString="Przhiboro, AA, Paramonov, NM, Bazova, N, 2009. Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae). In: Lantsov, V, Ed., Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889-1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909-1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909-1994). Zoosymposia 3: 221 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" title="Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" volume="3" volumeTitle="Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889 - 1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909 - 1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909 - 1994)." year="2009">Przhiboro et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Both sexes are attracted to light (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" author="Przhiboro, AA" editor="Lantsov, V" journalOrPublisher="Zoosymposia" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="221 - 228" refId="B47" refString="Przhiboro, AA, Paramonov, NM, Bazova, N, 2009. Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae). In: Lantsov, V, Ed., Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889-1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909-1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909-1994). Zoosymposia 3: 221 - 228, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" title="Distribution of Hexatoma (Eriocera) ussuriensis Alexander (Diptera: Limoniidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zoosymposia.3.1.18" volume="3" volumeTitle="Crane flies. History, taxonomy and ecology (Diptera: Tipulidae, Limoniidae, Pediciidae, Trichoceridae, Ptychopteridae, Tanyderidae). Memorial volume dedicated to Dr. Charles Paul Alexander (1889 - 1981), Dr. Bernhard Mannheims (1909 - 1971) and Dr. Evgeniy Nikolaevich Savchenko (1909 - 1994)." year="2009">Przhiboro et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Larvae of this species develop only on the bottom of large and medium sized rivers. Last instar larvae and pupae can be found in the riparian zone, usually in gravel, sand or under stones in Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4021.1.4" author="Podeniene, V" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="165" pagination="93 - 118" refId="B46" refString="Podeniene, V, Gelhaus, JK, 2015. Review of the last instar larvae and pupae of Hexatoma (Eriocera) and Hexatoma (Hexatoma) (Diptera, Limoniidae, Limnophilinae). Zootaxa 4021 (1): 93 - 118, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4021.1.4" title="Review of the last instar larvae and pupae of Hexatoma (Eriocera) and Hexatoma (Hexatoma) (Diptera, Limoniidae, Limnophilinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4021.1.4" volume="4021" year="2015">Podeniene and Gelhaus 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Eastern part of Russia, Mongolia and Hokkaido Island, Japan. Recorded on the Korean Peninsula for the first time.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
